<paragraph blockId="7.[125,230,817,841]" box="[125,230,817,841]" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">
<emphasis box="[125,230,817,841]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,1172,866,923]" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">
Tip of arista broadened (
<figureCitation box="[404,523,866,890]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[125,185,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[126,1169,974,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-183@7.[125,1173,972,1602]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Phortica saltiaristula Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Arista; (B) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod and parameres (ventral view); (D) paramere (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221182/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">Figure 3A</figureCitation>
); right lateral lobe of vertical process of gonopod with one pointed projection basally (
<figureCitation box="[438,557,899,923]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[125,185,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[126,1169,974,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-183@7.[125,1173,972,1602]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Phortica saltiaristula Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Arista; (B) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod and parameres (ventral view); (D) paramere (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221182/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
); paramere strongly curved distally (
<figureCitation box="[977,1135,899,923]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[125,185,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[126,1169,974,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-183@7.[125,1173,972,1602]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Phortica saltiaristula Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Arista; (B) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod and parameres (ventral view); (D) paramere (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221182/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">Figure 3C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221182" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5221182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221182/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956" startId="7.[125,185,1637,1656]" targetBox="[126,1169,974,1598]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[125,1173,1637,1683]" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">
Figure 3. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen and Wen" authorityName="Chen and Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[220,545,1637,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saltiaristula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[220,398,1637,1656]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">Phortica saltiaristula</emphasis>
Chen and Wen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[555,630,1637,1656]" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis box="[638,652,1638,1657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="3956">„</emphasis>
. (A) Arista; (B) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod and parameres (ventral view); (D) paramere (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[138,1185,136,192]" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">
Some characters commonly seen also in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen, 2005" authorityName="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[630,800,136,160]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagittaristula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[630,800,136,160]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">P. sagittaristula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[807,897,136,160]" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are not referred to in the following description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[138,259,249,273]" box="[138,259,249,273]" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">
<emphasis box="[138,259,249,273]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[138,1177,297,321]" box="[138,1177,297,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">
<emphasis box="[138,249,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Third to fifth tergites each with a brown posterior band, interrupted medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[138,1185,362,481]" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">
<emphasis box="[138,323,362,386]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Vertical process of gonopod with left projection pointed, right projection round; apical processes slightly pointed (
<figureCitation box="[630,752,393,417]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[125,185,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[126,1169,974,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-183@7.[125,1173,972,1602]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Phortica saltiaristula Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Arista; (B) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod and parameres (ventral view); (D) paramere (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221182/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
). Paramere strongly curved distally, basally with two sensilla (
<figureCitation box="[429,588,425,449]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[125,185,1637,1656]" captionTargetBox="[126,1169,974,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-183@7.[125,1173,972,1602]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Phortica saltiaristula Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Arista; (B) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod and parameres (ventral view); (D) paramere (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221182/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">Figure 3C, D</figureCitation>
). Median rod of aedeagus very short, unsclerotized; outer membrane slightly developed.
</paragraph>
