</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[138,1185,1216,1304]" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen, 2005" authorityName="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[496,668,1216,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagittaristula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[496,668,1216,1240]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957">P. sagittaristula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[678,772,1216,1240]" pageId="8" pageNumber="3957" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having the arista without dorsal branches, and in the shape of the gonopod, but differs from the latter species by their diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
